WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.780 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.780 --> 00:00:08.126 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.126 --> 00:00:09.560 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.560 --> 00:00:13.140 align:middle line:90%
>> No one has it figured out.

00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:17.270 align:middle line:84%
And the belief and the
myth and the delusion

00:00:17.270 --> 00:00:19.520 align:middle line:84%
that somebody else
has it figured out

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:23.330 align:middle line:84%
is actually what
keeps us suffering.

00:00:23.330 --> 00:00:28.370 align:middle line:84%
I haven't met anyone, of
the true spiritual teachers

00:00:28.370 --> 00:00:31.897 align:middle line:84%
I've met, who have said
they have it figured out.

00:00:31.897 --> 00:00:34.230 align:middle line:84%
They say, oh my god, I don't
have it figured out at all.

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:37.218 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:37.218 --> 00:00:42.710 align:middle line:90%


00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:45.260 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe I'll reach a
place where I feel, oh, I'm

00:00:45.260 --> 00:00:49.820 align:middle line:90%
enough, in all areas.

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:52.970 align:middle line:90%
Enough as a partner.

00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:57.630 align:middle line:84%
In my work, of course, am
I enough as a provider,

00:00:57.630 --> 00:01:00.260 align:middle line:90%
a caregiver?

00:01:00.260 --> 00:01:04.510 align:middle line:84%
And this is no different
than everybody else I meet.

00:01:04.510 --> 00:01:08.020 align:middle line:84%
It's intriguing to me to
catch myself and notice

00:01:08.020 --> 00:01:14.440 align:middle line:84%
where it comes up in those
really insidious ways

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:15.380 align:middle line:90%
that I'm not enough.

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the
struggle I always have.

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:21.488 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:21.488 --> 00:01:28.960 align:middle line:90%


00:01:28.960 --> 00:01:34.330 align:middle line:84%
Growing up a Jewish gay man in
McKeesport, Pennsylvania, which

00:01:34.330 --> 00:01:37.540 align:middle line:84%
is a steel town, not
knowing how to throw

00:01:37.540 --> 00:01:42.460 align:middle line:84%
a football or a
baseball and not caring,

00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:45.680 align:middle line:84%
I was called all
kinds of things.

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:49.065 align:middle line:84%
And then, plus, I was a dancer,
and I was in the musicals.

00:01:49.065 --> 00:01:52.900 align:middle line:90%


00:01:52.900 --> 00:02:03.120 align:middle line:84%
Back then, I could not fathom
that I could get married.

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:10.919 align:middle line:90%


00:02:10.919 --> 00:02:13.940 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't fathom that I
could be loved, could love.

00:02:13.940 --> 00:02:16.695 align:middle line:90%


00:02:16.695 --> 00:02:18.070 align:middle line:84%
I didn't think I
could have cats.

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:21.180 align:middle line:90%


00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:23.224 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't a possibility.

00:02:23.224 --> 00:02:26.310 align:middle line:90%


00:02:26.310 --> 00:02:32.580 align:middle line:84%
And I say this I think with
a hundred percent conviction,

00:02:32.580 --> 00:02:35.320 align:middle line:84%
if you said being
gay wasn't enough--

00:02:35.320 --> 00:02:36.850 align:middle line:84%
you're gay, so
you're not enough--

00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:38.550 align:middle line:90%
back then, I believed it.

00:02:38.550 --> 00:02:39.965 align:middle line:90%
So I wasn't enough.

00:02:39.965 --> 00:02:46.050 align:middle line:90%


00:02:46.050 --> 00:02:49.290 align:middle line:84%
All of us who don't
feel enough believe

00:02:49.290 --> 00:02:52.567 align:middle line:84%
there is some way
it's supposed to be

00:02:52.567 --> 00:02:55.025 align:middle line:84%
and that we're telling ourselves
we're not living up to it.

00:02:55.025 --> 00:02:57.615 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:57.615 --> 00:03:01.320 align:middle line:90%


00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:02.820 align:middle line:84%
I think part of
the reason people

00:03:02.820 --> 00:03:04.500 align:middle line:84%
don't feel enough
is we get messages

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:08.210 align:middle line:84%
that you're only enough
if you look like this,

00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:11.270 align:middle line:84%
do this, look like this,
not physical appearance,

00:03:11.270 --> 00:03:13.460 align:middle line:84%
but your life looks
a certain way.

00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:14.880 align:middle line:90%
And so we're chasing that.

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:19.480 align:middle line:90%


00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:23.538 align:middle line:84%
It's freeing to realize
no one has it figured out.

00:03:23.538 --> 00:03:25.080 align:middle line:84%
Stop comparing
yourself to everybody.

00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:27.985 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:27.985 --> 00:03:42.460 align:middle line:90%


00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:45.065 align:middle line:84%
What confuses me about people
is when they say, well,

00:03:45.065 --> 00:03:46.190 align:middle line:90%
when will I get this right?

00:03:46.190 --> 00:03:47.440 align:middle line:90%
When will I be done with this?

00:03:47.440 --> 00:03:48.770 align:middle line:90%
And I say, when you're dead.

00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:50.330 align:middle line:90%
I can't speak to after that.

00:03:50.330 --> 00:03:51.650 align:middle line:90%
Maybe something goes on after.

00:03:51.650 --> 00:03:52.725 align:middle line:90%
But when you're dead.

00:03:52.725 --> 00:03:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And so I keep
thinking, I'm going

00:03:54.100 --> 00:03:56.642 align:middle line:84%
to be working on this for the
rest of my life, and that's OK.

00:03:56.642 --> 00:03:59.450 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:59.450 --> 00:04:03.880 align:middle line:90%


00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:07.810 align:middle line:84%
I'm a person who asks
myself every day,

00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:10.000 align:middle line:90%
how can I be of service?

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.400 align:middle line:90%
How can I be more compassionate?

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:16.660 align:middle line:84%
How can I be more at peace,
at ease with whatever happens?

00:04:16.660 --> 00:04:19.922 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:19.922 --> 00:04:21.329 align:middle line:90%


00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:25.260 align:middle line:84%
I keep thinking of
it all as a practice.

00:04:25.260 --> 00:04:27.300 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think
our existence is

00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:32.730 align:middle line:84%
any different than an artist,
a gymnast, an athlete.

00:04:32.730 --> 00:04:36.540 align:middle line:84%
They may be tired, but they go
back on the mat the next day

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:37.810 align:middle line:90%
and practice again.

00:04:37.810 --> 00:04:39.280 align:middle line:90%
They don't say, oh, I got it.

00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:40.160 align:middle line:90%
I'm perfect now.

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:43.456 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:43.456 --> 00:04:48.810 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:53.850 align:middle line:84%
I also don't think of
practice as lack of joy.

00:04:53.850 --> 00:04:56.010 align:middle line:84%
The analogy I
often say to myself

00:04:56.010 --> 00:04:59.170 align:middle line:90%
is it's like learning to drive.

00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:00.940 align:middle line:90%
That was difficult for me.

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:02.080 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to do it.

00:05:02.080 --> 00:05:03.160 align:middle line:90%
But, yes, I did.

00:05:03.160 --> 00:05:04.090 align:middle line:90%
I did.

00:05:04.090 --> 00:05:05.080 align:middle line:90%
I was scared.

00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:06.400 align:middle line:90%
I was gripping the wheel.

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:07.700 align:middle line:90%
But I'm like, I want freedom.

00:05:07.700 --> 00:05:10.620 align:middle line:90%


00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:12.030 align:middle line:90%
So that's the same analogy.

00:05:12.030 --> 00:05:15.260 align:middle line:84%
It's like, I want
to be at peace.

00:05:15.260 --> 00:05:16.735 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do that again.

00:05:16.735 --> 00:05:18.235 align:middle line:84%
I want to practice
doing that again.

00:05:18.235 --> 00:05:21.444 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:21.444 --> 00:05:25.280 align:middle line:90%


00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:30.920 align:middle line:84%
Every one of us can practice
being kinder and gentler

00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:32.100 align:middle line:90%
to ourselves.

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:35.088 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:35.088 --> 00:05:51.560 align:middle line:90%


00:05:51.560 --> 00:05:56.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm still puzzled
by people who think

00:05:56.780 --> 00:05:58.470 align:middle line:90%
they're never going to die.

00:05:58.470 --> 00:06:01.320 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:01.320 --> 00:06:06.560 align:middle line:90%


00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:08.820 align:middle line:90%
You're going to die.

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's exciting
because then you

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:17.030 align:middle line:84%
can infuse this moment, when
you remember, with meaning.

00:06:17.030 --> 00:06:19.940 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:24.310 align:middle line:90%


00:06:24.310 --> 00:06:26.680 align:middle line:84%
My daily mantra is a
question to myself of,

00:06:26.680 --> 00:06:30.980 align:middle line:84%
how do you want to
be in this moment?

00:06:30.980 --> 00:06:35.420 align:middle line:84%
And that's, I think,
that North Star for me

00:06:35.420 --> 00:06:40.760 align:middle line:84%
that I cling to to help
me navigate my life.

00:06:40.760 --> 00:06:43.694 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:43.694 --> 00:06:48.100 align:middle line:90%


00:06:48.100 --> 00:06:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Whatever you feel connected
with, you're engaging,

00:06:52.880 --> 00:06:54.645 align:middle line:90%
you're leaning into it.

00:06:54.645 --> 00:06:57.360 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:57.360 --> 00:06:59.290 align:middle line:90%


00:06:59.290 --> 00:07:06.470 align:middle line:84%
For me, that's making tea,
having Murphy sit on my lap.

00:07:06.470 --> 00:07:10.360 align:middle line:84%
They're all helping me
get out of rumination

00:07:10.360 --> 00:07:11.870 align:middle line:90%
and into the moment.

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:14.360 align:middle line:84%
Because in the moment, I
feel the weight of this cat.

00:07:14.360 --> 00:07:15.785 align:middle line:90%
I feel their purring.

00:07:15.785 --> 00:07:18.745 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:18.745 --> 00:07:24.690 align:middle line:90%


00:07:24.690 --> 00:07:29.220 align:middle line:84%
They're grounding
experiences about saying,

00:07:29.220 --> 00:07:30.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm here right now.

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:33.844 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:33.844 --> 00:07:46.710 align:middle line:90%


00:07:46.710 --> 00:07:55.620 align:middle line:84%
The way I think of peace is
not devoid of pain or dislike

00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:57.510 align:middle line:90%
or displeasure.

00:07:57.510 --> 00:08:01.510 align:middle line:84%
It's that there's no
fight, no struggle.

00:08:01.510 --> 00:08:03.810 align:middle line:84%
I think of it like if
two warring nations--

00:08:03.810 --> 00:08:06.030 align:middle line:84%
I can think of
several right now--

00:08:06.030 --> 00:08:10.110 align:middle line:84%
were to have a peace
agreement, the people might not

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:13.570 align:middle line:84%
like each other, they
might still criticize,

00:08:13.570 --> 00:08:17.530 align:middle line:84%
but they don't throw rocks
or bombs at each other.

00:08:17.530 --> 00:08:21.020 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think
it's hyperbole to say,

00:08:21.020 --> 00:08:24.940 align:middle line:84%
I think that we drop bombs
on ourselves all day long

00:08:24.940 --> 00:08:27.975 align:middle line:84%
and twist ourselves into
knots trying to be enough.

00:08:27.975 --> 00:08:33.669 align:middle line:90%


00:08:33.669 --> 00:08:39.610 align:middle line:84%
For me, peace is just being
able to breathe with ease

00:08:39.610 --> 00:08:48.790 align:middle line:84%
and embrace the behaviors
that I would like to change,

00:08:48.790 --> 00:08:55.810 align:middle line:84%
embrace the situation that
is not necessarily the one

00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:57.020 align:middle line:90%
I would like.

00:08:57.020 --> 00:08:59.768 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:59.768 --> 00:09:01.150 align:middle line:90%


00:09:01.150 --> 00:09:05.260 align:middle line:84%
I often say to myself in
my meditations every day,

00:09:05.260 --> 00:09:09.790 align:middle line:84%
may I be safe, may I be
at peace and at ease.

00:09:09.790 --> 00:09:13.742 align:middle line:84%
May I be healthy,
not just physically,

00:09:13.742 --> 00:09:15.200 align:middle line:84%
mentally, emotionally,
spiritually.

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:23.200 align:middle line:84%
And then the phrase
that I have changed,

00:09:23.200 --> 00:09:27.210 align:middle line:84%
tweaked it a little
bit, is, and may

00:09:27.210 --> 00:09:29.765 align:middle line:90%
I go gently knowing my goodness.

00:09:29.765 --> 00:09:32.615 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:32.615 --> 00:09:37.380 align:middle line:90%


00:09:37.380 --> 00:09:40.775 align:middle line:84%
Knowing our goodness goes
back to being enough.

00:09:40.775 --> 00:09:45.240 align:middle line:90%


00:09:45.240 --> 00:09:50.820 align:middle line:84%
For me, I'm getting
to know my goodness.

00:09:50.820 --> 00:09:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And when I say that, since
I believe it's a process,

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:04.190 align:middle line:84%
I can be at peace with
that most of the time.

00:10:04.190 --> 00:10:23.000 align:middle line:90%